[
  {
    "text": "\"Robam kbach boran,\"",
    "start": 12.58,
    "duration": 1.776
  },
  {
    "text": "or the art of Khmer classical dance,",
    "start": 14.38,
    "duration": 1.776
  },
  {
    "text": "is more than 1,000 years old.",
    "start": 16.18,
    "duration": 1.8
  },
  {
    "text": "It was developed as a prayer in movement",
    "start": 18.82,
    "duration": 2.576
  },
  {
    "text": "for rain and fertility,",
    "start": 21.42,
    "duration": 2.176
  },
  {
    "text": "and a prosperity that this meant\nfor an agricultural society.",
    "start": 23.62,
    "duration": 3.4
  },
  {
    "text": "Dancers who were both men and women",
    "start": 28.82,
    "duration": 2.736
  },
  {
    "text": "were offered to temples",
    "start": 31.58,
    "duration": 1.256
  },
  {
    "text": "where they served as living bridges\nbetween heaven and earth.",
    "start": 32.86,
    "duration": 3.08
  },
  {
    "text": "Their dancing bodies carried the prayers\nof the people up to the gods,",
    "start": 36.62,
    "duration": 4.936
  },
  {
    "text": "and the will of the deities\nwas delivered back through them",
    "start": 41.58,
    "duration": 3.376
  },
  {
    "text": "to the people and the land.",
    "start": 44.98,
    "duration": 1.52
  },
  {
    "text": "There are a lot of curves in Khmer dance.",
    "start": 49.54,
    "duration": 2.8
  },
  {
    "text": "Our backs are arched,",
    "start": 53.26,
    "duration": 1.52
  },
  {
    "text": "our knees are bent,",
    "start": 55.58,
    "duration": 1.896
  },
  {
    "text": "our toes are curled,",
    "start": 57.5,
    "duration": 2.016
  },
  {
    "text": "our elbows are hyperflexed",
    "start": 59.54,
    "duration": 2.336
  },
  {
    "text": "and our fingers are curved backwards.",
    "start": 61.9,
    "duration": 2.44
  },
  {
    "text": "All of these curves\ncreate a serpentine impression,",
    "start": 65.42,
    "duration": 3.656
  },
  {
    "text": "and this is important because before\nthe introduction of major religions,",
    "start": 69.1,
    "duration": 4.776
  },
  {
    "text": "Khmers, and people all over the world\npracticed animism.",
    "start": 73.9,
    "duration": 5.76
  },
  {
    "text": "Serpents were especially important\nin this belief system",
    "start": 80.94,
    "duration": 2.896
  },
  {
    "text": "because in their fluid,\ncurvilinear movement,",
    "start": 83.86,
    "duration": 4.376
  },
  {
    "text": "they mimicked the flow of water.",
    "start": 88.26,
    "duration": 1.64
  },
  {
    "text": "So to invoke the serpent\nin your dancing body then",
    "start": 91.34,
    "duration": 3.536
  },
  {
    "text": "was to conjure the image\nof rivers cutting across the earth:",
    "start": 94.9,
    "duration": 3.76
  },
  {
    "text": "inspire the flow of life-giving waters.",
    "start": 99.5,
    "duration": 2.96
  },
  {
    "text": "As you can see then,",
    "start": 105.26,
    "duration": 1.296
  },
  {
    "text": "Khmer classical dance\nis a transformation of nature,",
    "start": 106.58,
    "duration": 3.416
  },
  {
    "text": "of both the physical world around us\nand of our own internal universe.",
    "start": 110.02,
    "duration": 4.12
  },
  {
    "text": "We have four primary\nhand gestures that we use.",
    "start": 115.1,
    "duration": 2.976
  },
  {
    "text": "Can we do them together?",
    "start": 118.1,
    "duration": 1.2
  },
  {
    "text": "Yeah? OK.",
    "start": 120.46,
    "duration": 1.36
  },
  {
    "text": "This is a tree.",
    "start": 123.9,
    "duration": 1.88
  },
  {
    "text": "That tree will grow,",
    "start": 127.5,
    "duration": 1.52
  },
  {
    "text": "and then it will have leaves.",
    "start": 130.3,
    "duration": 3.04
  },
  {
    "text": "After it has leaves,",
    "start": 134.42,
    "duration": 1.536
  },
  {
    "text": "it'll have flowers,",
    "start": 135.98,
    "duration": 2.72
  },
  {
    "text": "and after it has flowers,",
    "start": 139.78,
    "duration": 2.296
  },
  {
    "text": "it'll have fruit.",
    "start": 142.1,
    "duration": 1.72
  },
  {
    "text": "That fruit will drop",
    "start": 144.7,
    "duration": 2.336
  },
  {
    "text": "and a new tree will grow.",
    "start": 147.06,
    "duration": 2.016
  },
  {
    "text": "And in those four gestures",
    "start": 149.1,
    "duration": 2.056
  },
  {
    "text": "is the cycle of life.",
    "start": 151.18,
    "duration": 1.6
  },
  {
    "text": "These four gestures are then used",
    "start": 160.74,
    "duration": 2.616
  },
  {
    "text": "to create a whole entire language\nwith which dancers express themselves.",
    "start": 163.38,
    "duration": 4.656
  },
  {
    "text": "So for example,",
    "start": 168.06,
    "duration": 1.296
  },
  {
    "text": "I can say,",
    "start": 169.38,
    "duration": 1.336
  },
  {
    "text": "\"I.\"",
    "start": 170.74,
    "duration": 1.2
  },
  {
    "text": "\"I.\"",
    "start": 172.82,
    "duration": 1.2
  },
  {
    "text": "In dance that would be ...",
    "start": 174.5,
    "duration": 1.44
  },
  {
    "text": "\"I.\"",
    "start": 178.54,
    "duration": 1.576
  },
  {
    "text": "Or I can say ...",
    "start": 180.14,
    "duration": 1.2
  },
  {
    "text": "\"Hey you, come here, come here.\"",
    "start": 183.26,
    "duration": 2.936
  },
  {
    "text": "In dance ...",
    "start": 186.22,
    "duration": 1.2
  },
  {
    "text": "\"Come here,\"",
    "start": 191.26,
    "duration": 1.256
  },
  {
    "text": "or, \"Go, go.\"",
    "start": 192.54,
    "duration": 1.896
  },
  {
    "text": "(Laughter)",
    "start": 194.46,
    "duration": 1.2
  },
  {
    "text": "\"Go.\"",
    "start": 198.7,
    "duration": 1.416
  },
  {
    "text": "And everything from ...",
    "start": 200.14,
    "duration": 1.24
  },
  {
    "text": "love ...",
    "start": 204.1,
    "duration": 1.2
  },
  {
    "text": "to sadness,",
    "start": 211.1,
    "duration": 1.28
  },
  {
    "text": "to --",
    "start": 213.3,
    "duration": 1.216
  },
  {
    "text": "(Stomping)",
    "start": 214.54,
    "duration": 1.016
  },
  {
    "text": "anger",
    "start": 215.58,
    "duration": 1.336
  },
  {
    "text": "can be expressed\nthrough the dance as well.",
    "start": 216.94,
    "duration": 2.24
  },
  {
    "text": "There's a certain magic",
    "start": 221.98,
    "duration": 1.656
  },
  {
    "text": "in the way that things are filtered,\ntransformed and put together",
    "start": 223.66,
    "duration": 4.136
  },
  {
    "text": "to create limitless possibilities in art.",
    "start": 227.82,
    "duration": 2.64
  },
  {
    "text": "The Khmer word for art,",
    "start": 231.42,
    "duration": 1.736
  },
  {
    "text": "silapak,",
    "start": 233.18,
    "duration": 1.216
  },
  {
    "text": "in fact, at its root, means \"magic.\"",
    "start": 234.42,
    "duration": 2.6
  },
  {
    "text": "The artist --",
    "start": 238.14,
    "duration": 1.216
  },
  {
    "text": "the silapakar,",
    "start": 239.38,
    "duration": 1.496
  },
  {
    "text": "or the silapakarani, then,",
    "start": 240.9,
    "duration": 1.416
  },
  {
    "text": "is nothing short of a magician.",
    "start": 242.34,
    "duration": 2.16
  },
  {
    "text": "I am very proud to say",
    "start": 246.18,
    "duration": 1.936
  },
  {
    "text": "that I belong to a long line of magicians,",
    "start": 248.14,
    "duration": 3.016
  },
  {
    "text": "from my teacher, Sophiline Cheam Shapiro,",
    "start": 251.18,
    "duration": 2.28
  },
  {
    "text": "to her teachers who were stars\nin the royal palace,",
    "start": 254.3,
    "duration": 3.04
  },
  {
    "text": "to the ancient dancers of Angkor",
    "start": 258.18,
    "duration": 2.776
  },
  {
    "text": "and to the primal villagers",
    "start": 260.98,
    "duration": 1.536
  },
  {
    "text": "from which the art form\noriginally took life.",
    "start": 262.54,
    "duration": 2.56
  },
  {
    "text": "That said,",
    "start": 267.3,
    "duration": 1.216
  },
  {
    "text": "our cherished heritage was once\nalmost completely destroyed.",
    "start": 268.54,
    "duration": 3.76
  },
  {
    "text": "If you are wearing glasses,",
    "start": 276.58,
    "duration": 1.776
  },
  {
    "text": "please stand up.",
    "start": 278.38,
    "duration": 1.2
  },
  {
    "text": "If you speak more than one language,",
    "start": 284.58,
    "duration": 2.376
  },
  {
    "text": "please stand up.",
    "start": 286.98,
    "duration": 1.2
  },
  {
    "text": "If you have light skin,",
    "start": 293.14,
    "duration": 1.576
  },
  {
    "text": "please stand up.",
    "start": 294.74,
    "duration": 1.2
  },
  {
    "text": "Your glasses meant\nthat you could afford health care.",
    "start": 303.62,
    "duration": 3.24
  },
  {
    "text": "That second or third language you spoke\nindicated your elite education.",
    "start": 308.78,
    "duration": 4.48
  },
  {
    "text": "Your light skin meant\nyou didn't have to work beneath the sun.",
    "start": 315.14,
    "duration": 3.4
  },
  {
    "text": "Under the Khmer Rouge,",
    "start": 319.86,
    "duration": 1.536
  },
  {
    "text": "who took over Cambodia from 1975 to 1979,",
    "start": 321.42,
    "duration": 4.336
  },
  {
    "text": "we would all be dead now,",
    "start": 325.78,
    "duration": 2.176
  },
  {
    "text": "targeted because of our assumed privilege.",
    "start": 327.98,
    "duration": 2.88
  },
  {
    "text": "You see,",
    "start": 336.98,
    "duration": 1.216
  },
  {
    "text": "the Khmer Rouge looked to Cambodia,",
    "start": 338.22,
    "duration": 2.136
  },
  {
    "text": "and they saw centuries\nof rigid inequality.",
    "start": 340.38,
    "duration": 3.616
  },
  {
    "text": "The king and the few elites around him",
    "start": 344.02,
    "duration": 2.176
  },
  {
    "text": "had all the pleasures\nand comforts of the world",
    "start": 346.22,
    "duration": 2.856
  },
  {
    "text": "while the mass majority\nsuffered from backbreaking labor",
    "start": 349.1,
    "duration": 3.216
  },
  {
    "text": "and harsh poverty.",
    "start": 352.34,
    "duration": 1.24
  },
  {
    "text": "You don't need a history book\nto see that this is true.",
    "start": 354.54,
    "duration": 2.64
  },
  {
    "text": "The Khmer word for \"I,\"",
    "start": 357.94,
    "duration": 2.216
  },
  {
    "text": "for \"me,\"",
    "start": 360.18,
    "duration": 1.2
  },
  {
    "text": "is khnhom.",
    "start": 362.3,
    "duration": 1.36
  },
  {
    "text": "This very same word can also mean \"slave\"",
    "start": 365.06,
    "duration": 3.696
  },
  {
    "text": "and dancers were in fact known\nas knhom preah robam,",
    "start": 368.78,
    "duration": 3.736
  },
  {
    "text": "or \"slaves of the sacred dance.\"",
    "start": 372.54,
    "duration": 2.6
  },
  {
    "text": "The Khmer Rouge sought\nto end slavery in Cambodia,",
    "start": 377.02,
    "duration": 3.056
  },
  {
    "text": "yet somehow they turned\neveryone into slaves to do it.",
    "start": 380.1,
    "duration": 3.48
  },
  {
    "text": "They became the oppression\nthat they sought to end.",
    "start": 384.22,
    "duration": 3.0
  },
  {
    "text": "They evacuated the capital",
    "start": 388.18,
    "duration": 1.696
  },
  {
    "text": "and forced people into labor camps.",
    "start": 389.9,
    "duration": 2.496
  },
  {
    "text": "They tore families apart",
    "start": 392.42,
    "duration": 1.896
  },
  {
    "text": "and brainwashed children\nagainst their own parents.",
    "start": 394.34,
    "duration": 2.76
  },
  {
    "text": "Everywhere, people were dying\nand being killed,",
    "start": 397.9,
    "duration": 3.256
  },
  {
    "text": "losing their lives from disease,",
    "start": 401.18,
    "duration": 2.056
  },
  {
    "text": "overwork,",
    "start": 403.26,
    "duration": 1.216
  },
  {
    "text": "execution and starvation.",
    "start": 404.5,
    "duration": 2.0
  },
  {
    "text": "The result of this is that an entire third\nof Cambodia's population was lost",
    "start": 408.46,
    "duration": 4.696
  },
  {
    "text": "in less than four years,",
    "start": 413.18,
    "duration": 1.816
  },
  {
    "text": "and in that number were 90 percent\nof Khmer dance artists.",
    "start": 415.02,
    "duration": 3.84
  },
  {
    "text": "In other words,",
    "start": 420.1,
    "duration": 1.216
  },
  {
    "text": "nine out of 10 visions\nfor the tradition and future were lost.",
    "start": 421.34,
    "duration": 4.6
  },
  {
    "text": "Thankfully, however,",
    "start": 427.58,
    "duration": 1.696
  },
  {
    "text": "it was my teacher's teachers,",
    "start": 429.3,
    "duration": 2.056
  },
  {
    "text": "Chea Samy, Soth Sam On and Chheng Phon,",
    "start": 431.38,
    "duration": 3.736
  },
  {
    "text": "who would lead the revival of the art form",
    "start": 435.14,
    "duration": 2.056
  },
  {
    "text": "from the ashes of war and genocide:",
    "start": 437.22,
    "duration": 2.24
  },
  {
    "text": "one student,",
    "start": 440.58,
    "duration": 1.536
  },
  {
    "text": "one gesture,",
    "start": 442.14,
    "duration": 1.576
  },
  {
    "text": "one dance at a time.",
    "start": 443.74,
    "duration": 1.976
  },
  {
    "text": "They wrote the love,",
    "start": 445.74,
    "duration": 1.896
  },
  {
    "text": "magic,",
    "start": 447.66,
    "duration": 1.456
  },
  {
    "text": "beauty,",
    "start": 449.14,
    "duration": 1.216
  },
  {
    "text": "history and philosophy of our lineage",
    "start": 450.38,
    "duration": 2.336
  },
  {
    "text": "into the bodies of the next generation.",
    "start": 452.74,
    "duration": 2.48
  },
  {
    "text": "Nearly 40 years later,",
    "start": 457.46,
    "duration": 1.896
  },
  {
    "text": "Khmer classical dance\nhas been revived to new heights.",
    "start": 459.38,
    "duration": 3.52
  },
  {
    "text": "Yet somehow it still exists\nin a vulnerable environment.",
    "start": 463.9,
    "duration": 3.56
  },
  {
    "text": "The disastrous effects of war\nstill haunt Khmer people today.",
    "start": 468.46,
    "duration": 4.176
  },
  {
    "text": "It is written in our bodies,",
    "start": 472.66,
    "duration": 2.096
  },
  {
    "text": "manifested in a genetic passage of PTSD",
    "start": 474.78,
    "duration": 3.536
  },
  {
    "text": "and in families facing cyclical poverty",
    "start": 478.34,
    "duration": 2.776
  },
  {
    "text": "and immense cultural rifts\nand language barriers.",
    "start": 481.14,
    "duration": 2.72
  },
  {
    "text": "Yet beauty is a most resilient thing.",
    "start": 486.58,
    "duration": 2.64
  },
  {
    "text": "Beauty has this ability\nto grow anywhere and everywhere",
    "start": 490.9,
    "duration": 3.856
  },
  {
    "text": "at any time.",
    "start": 494.78,
    "duration": 1.2
  },
  {
    "text": "Beauty is what connects people\nthrough time and place.",
    "start": 497.38,
    "duration": 3.64
  },
  {
    "text": "Beauty is a liberation from suffering.",
    "start": 502.46,
    "duration": 3.08
  },
  {
    "text": "As Khmer artists work to revive\nour culture and country,",
    "start": 508.22,
    "duration": 3.576
  },
  {
    "text": "we find that there are many paths\nin which to move forward into the future.",
    "start": 511.82,
    "duration": 4.24
  },
  {
    "text": "And in a tradition where we often\ndon't know the dancer's names,",
    "start": 517.82,
    "duration": 4.336
  },
  {
    "text": "who they were,",
    "start": 522.18,
    "duration": 1.216
  },
  {
    "text": "what their lives were like,",
    "start": 523.42,
    "duration": 1.496
  },
  {
    "text": "what they felt,",
    "start": 524.94,
    "duration": 1.856
  },
  {
    "text": "let me propose that we move forward\nhonestly and openly from \"khnhom.\"",
    "start": 526.82,
    "duration": 5.2
  },
  {
    "text": "Khnhom not as in slave,",
    "start": 533.34,
    "duration": 2.056
  },
  {
    "text": "but as in conscious service.",
    "start": 535.42,
    "duration": 1.92
  },
  {
    "text": "Khnhom:",
    "start": 538.54,
    "duration": 1.496
  },
  {
    "text": "\"I,\"",
    "start": 540.06,
    "duration": 1.616
  },
  {
    "text": "\"me,\"",
    "start": 541.7,
    "duration": 1.496
  },
  {
    "text": "\"flowering.\"",
    "start": 543.22,
    "duration": 1.2
  },
  {
    "text": "My name is Prumsodun Ok.",
    "start": 546.34,
    "duration": 2.256
  },
  {
    "text": "I am Khmer,",
    "start": 548.62,
    "duration": 1.216
  },
  {
    "text": "and I am American.",
    "start": 549.86,
    "duration": 1.976
  },
  {
    "text": "I am the child of refugees,",
    "start": 551.86,
    "duration": 2.336
  },
  {
    "text": "a creator, a healer,",
    "start": 554.22,
    "duration": 1.936
  },
  {
    "text": "and a builder of bridges.",
    "start": 556.18,
    "duration": 1.72
  },
  {
    "text": "I am my teacher's first male student",
    "start": 558.7,
    "duration": 2.376
  },
  {
    "text": "in a tradition understood\nby many as female,",
    "start": 561.1,
    "duration": 3.296
  },
  {
    "text": "and I founded Cambodia's first\ngay dance company.",
    "start": 564.42,
    "duration": 3.08
  },
  {
    "text": "I am the incarnation\nof the beauty, dreams and power",
    "start": 568.62,
    "duration": 4.176
  },
  {
    "text": "of those who came before me.",
    "start": 572.82,
    "duration": 1.936
  },
  {
    "text": "The convergence\nof past, present and future,",
    "start": 574.78,
    "duration": 3.496
  },
  {
    "text": "and of individual and collective.",
    "start": 578.3,
    "duration": 2.44
  },
  {
    "text": "Let me then play\nthat ancient and ageless role",
    "start": 582.9,
    "duration": 3.216
  },
  {
    "text": "of the artist as messenger,",
    "start": 586.14,
    "duration": 2.096
  },
  {
    "text": "by sharing the words of Chheng Phon",
    "start": 588.26,
    "duration": 2.24
  },
  {
    "text": "\"A garden with only one type of flower,",
    "start": 592.06,
    "duration": 3.576
  },
  {
    "text": "or flowers of only one color,",
    "start": 595.66,
    "duration": 2.016
  },
  {
    "text": "is no good.\"",
    "start": 597.7,
    "duration": 1.2
  },
  {
    "text": "This is a reminder that our strength,",
    "start": 600.46,
    "duration": 2.88
  },
  {
    "text": "growth,",
    "start": 604.02,
    "duration": 1.216
  },
  {
    "text": "survival",
    "start": 605.26,
    "duration": 1.216
  },
  {
    "text": "and very existence,",
    "start": 606.5,
    "duration": 1.216
  },
  {
    "text": "lies in diversity.",
    "start": 607.74,
    "duration": 1.36
  },
  {
    "text": "It is, however,",
    "start": 610.5,
    "duration": 1.256
  },
  {
    "text": "a message of courage as well.",
    "start": 611.78,
    "duration": 1.8
  },
  {
    "text": "For a flower does not ask\nfor anyone's permission to bloom.",
    "start": 615.02,
    "duration": 3.68
  },
  {
    "text": "It was born to offer itself to the world.",
    "start": 619.82,
    "duration": 2.6
  },
  {
    "text": "Fearless love is its nature.",
    "start": 623.3,
    "duration": 2.84
  },
  {
    "text": "Thank you.",
    "start": 626.7,
    "duration": 1.216
  },
  {
    "text": "(Applause)",
    "start": 627.94,
    "duration": 5.36
  }
]